bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I have always taken an interest in taking care of children! I used to be in a program in middle school where we'd go to the next door elementary school and help tutor the little kids. I've babysat for many different families and I truly enjoy it! Getting to meet different kids, getting to have fun with them, and helping them with school work is something I always look forward to do everyday. I can honestly say that I am finally happy with the career path I'm taking! At least for now that I'm currently figuring life out!!

description.originalText: punctual. took care of my two kids on a last minute booking. will book again

bio.experienceSummary: I have 8 years of experience. I can help with Travel and Laundry. Basically if you need it I can accomplish it. I've always had a heart for children. I worked as a Medical Assistant in pediatrics for three years and a Lactation Consultant for a year. I will be starting as a Registered Nurse in the next few months. I am looking for some extra hours of work and I have recently moved from Florida and missing spending time helping with children.

Hello Parents! My name is Alysa and I have around three years of child care experience. I have babysat overnight and I've watched over multiple children at a time, so I am experienced enough and willing to be flexible. I will also be open to helping out with chores around the house and caring for pets in the home as well! I'll make sure to deliver a safe and fun time :))

Hi! My name is Emma and I am a senior at SCAD, studying graphic design and art history. I am new to Atlanta, reverently moved from Savannah, and am hoping to continue being a helping hand to families in the Midtown area. I have several years of experience as well as 2 younger siblings, whom I adore and have cared for full time during my time home. I am happy to work with children of all ages, pets of all kinds, as well as keeping up with daily housekeeping tasks. I am first aid trained, I do not smoke/vape, and my schedule is flexible. My ultimate goal is to foster a safe and uplifting environment for your little ones, and to be a positive role model in any and every way possible. I look forward to hearing from you to discuss how I can help! :)

description.displayText: I found Emma about 2 year's ago through a friend of mine who employed her as well. She was always dependable, on time, and would stay late as needed when I was running behind on work or errands. As a single mother, I really appreciated the extra help and care Emma provided and feel so lucky to have found her. Not to mention my girls adore her, she was always doing fun activities with them and was a great help with homework/school activities as well. We miss her very much since she moved to Savannah but I know she will be a blessing to the next family!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! I'm a licensed social worker pursuing a career in education, currently working on my second master's degree. 

I have over 5 years of experience working with children of all ages. 

My background in psychology gives me ample knowledge of child development and neurodivergence. 

I also have a lot of empathy and the ability to stay calm in stressful situations, because in this job, you never know what you'll see. 

Will do light house work, meal prep, take care of pets, and of course, make sure your little ones are safe!

Availability flexible once I leave my job! Will be away 5/2-5/18, but otherwise free.

**NOT CURRENTLY TAKING NEW POSITIONS***

I have 10 years of experience as a nanny/babysitter in Ohio. I've cared for children of all ages throughout college (from 4 months up to elementary age). I was a first grade teacher after graduating college, and then returned to nannying full-time during the pandemic.

Since 2020, I worked with one family who now has 3 kids. At the time I started working with them, their second child was just a few months old. I've watched their children grow over the years and was there to welcome a new baby to the family. They're still a second family to me. 

I now work a full-time job in a different career path, but would like to find a great family to help on a part-time/occasional basis, mostly on weekends. I'm comfortable with anything you need, I can do cooking and cleaning/house chores in addition to entertaining the kids with educational/developmentally appropriate activities.

Hello! My name is Nia and I am a fun, caring, mature, and reliable babysitter. I am a recent college graduate from Florida State University. I am currently working for Boys and Girls Clubs of America in Midtown Atlanta. I have years of experience working with kids of all ages, ranging from infants to young teens. I can provide my own transportation and I have a clean good driving record, if I am needed for transportation for your child to any activities. I do not mind light housekeeping/cleaning and cooking. If you are a family who is looking for a babysitter for after-school, date nights or weekend evenings to yourself, than I am the babysitter available for the position! Thank you very much for the opportunity!

Hi, my name is Sarah. I am currently a pediatric dental assistant. I have experience all ages of children. I was previously a nanny for a 3-month-old up until he recently turned 2! I love being fun and artsy with the little ones.

I am currently a graduate student at Columbia University pursuing my MA in Clinical Psychology. I have a BA from Vassar College in Neuroscience with a focus on learning and behavior. I have over 10 years of babysitting, tutoring, volunteer teaching, and dog walking experience! I spent several summers lifeguarding and teaching swimming at a day camp, and I babysat throughout highschool and college. I love hiking, cooking, gardening, painting, learning languages, and writing music. Please let me know if you would like any additional information about my childcare experience. I am more than happy to provide references!

description.displayText: Leah has been amazing with our 1-year-old.  Our daughter is hesitant around new people, and Leah was so kind and patient with her.  She always goes above and beyond and has been graciously flexible with our crazy schedule.  I would not hesitate to recommend her to other families.

Heyy parents! My name is Grace  (20 years old) I'm currently working towards getting my Insurance Adjusters License! Youngest of 13 and an Auntie to 15! Probably why I'm a pro at this! I'm here hoping to be the best hands-on help, pushing to making y'all's lives as parents easier!

~I hair as well(braids, curls, ponytails) pretty much anything you can name.
~I have plenty experience with cooking; I also do house cleaning(prepared with most of the Cleanings supplies.
~I can also do household assistance. (Clean house, cook, or run errands)
~~I hope this catches your interest! Thank you!! I also have a reference list on hand if needed

description.originalText: Grace has worked with our family for almost 3 years now!  Sadly we are moving but we still want to see her be great! She amazing, like all the others are saying. She’s so attentive and caring to my three children it almost feels like she’s apart of the family!
